  "texts": [
    "We call the (m, σ) a signature.",
    "• b ← Vrfy(pk, (m, σ)), and b = 1 or 0. if b = 1, we call (m, σ) an efficient signature.",
    "For an adversary, the key aim is to forge a signature with the correct output under the Vrfy algorithm without using the secret key for signing.",
    "In this context, digital signatures are generally categorized into one-time signatures and many-time signatures.",
    "As the literal meaning suggests, a one-time signature is designed to perform only a single signing operation, implying that for each signing and verification, a new key pair must be generated."
  ],
